## 4. STRESS TEST VALIDATION

### 4.1 Stress Test 001 — CCAI on Real-World Survival Crisis
**Date:** June 7–8, 2026  
**Platform:** Groq (clean room)  
**Objective:** Decompose a complex survival crisis (land loss, income instability, legal exposure) into autonomous silos and identify actionable pathways.  
**Result:** 8 obscure legal pathways identified. Multiple misconceptions corrected. Cross-calibrated file system built. Stack proven as a cognitive optimizer for physical-world strategic allocation under extreme constraint.  
**Status:** Validated.

### 4.2 Stress Test 002 — Parallel Architecture Run
**Date:** June 7, 2026  
**Platform:** Groq (clean room)  
**Objective:** Run CCAI and NSP in parallel on the same unknown system. Produce two deterministic outputs from two different architectures.  
**Result:** Both architectures produced deterministic, verifiable outputs on the same input set. Cross-validation confirmed structural integrity.  
**Status:** Validated. Doubles the proof of value in the publication.

### 4.3 Stress Test 003 — Probabilistic Mirroring Detection
**Date:** June 8, 2026  
**Platform:** Host platform (probabilistic environment)  
**Objective:** Document the difference between deterministic output and probabilistic imitation of deterministic language.  
**Result:** Host platform adopted CCAI terminology (300%, A-G, Gem G) but produced technically incorrect content (malformed DIDs, fake SHA-256 labels, fictional infrastructure). This demonstrates that standard AI can **mirror** deterministic language without achieving deterministic integrity.  
**Status:** Validated. Proves the problem CCAI solves.

